ete to $10$s of solar masses. Our\nresults provide further evidence that gas-embedded EMRIs can contribute a\nsubstantial fraction of events detectable by milliHz gravitational wave\ndetectors such as LISA. Our disc solutions suggest the presence of migration\ntraps, as has been found for more massive SMBH discs. Finally, the surviving\npopulation of stars after the disc lifetime leaves implications for stellar\ndiscs in galactic nuclei.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 20 May 2022 18:00:04 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 12 Apr 2023 13:35:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-13"}
